AI-Powered Gmail Reply Agent — Feasibility & Architecture Yes, this is feasible. Gmail exposes stable APIs, OAuth2 is well understood, and OpenRouter (or a single provider) can cover GPT / Claude / Gemini with one client. A bootcamp-size MVP is realistic if you cap scope: one user, drafts only, Postgres (or SQLite), and rule-based + LLM classification. Feasibility assessment Area Verdict Notes Read & thread context Highly feasible threads.get + users.messages with format=full Drafts (no auto-send) Highly feasible drafts.create with proper MIME; aligns with your spec Style learning Feasible (bounded) Last N Sent messages + prompt snippets; optional small embedding store later OpenRouter (multi-LLM) Feasible Single HTTP API; model string switches provider Confidence score Feasible Ask LLM for a number; optional second pass for “calibration” OTP / no-reply / alerts Feasible Rules first (fast); LLM assist optional Send + threading Feasible (extra time) Requires send scope, headers; often phase 2 Challenges to plan for Token & scope lifecycle (refresh, revoke, expiry) Gmail rate limits and quotas (backoff, batching) Long threads (truncate + optional summarization) False confidence (always allow human review; store “needs review” in DB) High-level architecture flow ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ CLIENT LAYER (pick one for MVP) │ │ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ │ │ │ Web UI │ │ CLI │ │ Cron/Worker │ │ Browser Ext │ │ │ │ (optional) │ │ (optional) │ │ (optional) │ │ (optional) │ │ │ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ▼ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ API & AUTH LAYER (REST) │ │ Google OAuth2 → App session / JWT → RBAC (single user in MVP) │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ┌