rts for a bootcamp deadline. Alternative B — All-in-one container (modular monolith) + cron. Pros: one deploy, one README, best for your submission. Cons: vertical scale only (fine for MVP). Recommendation for submission: modular monolith + Docker Compose. Deliverables (match the brief you shared) Working app (at least local/Docker) Public GitHub link (when policy allows) README: setup, env vars, API list, design trade-offs Video: OAuth → one thread → draft in Gmail (or in DB) with confidence line Summary (one paragraph) The Gmail AI Reply Agent is highly feasible with Gmail API + OpenRouter, a small relational schema, a clear draft-only policy, a classifier for no-reply/OTP mail, a simple style block from Sent mail, and a confidence gate that drives whether you create a Gmail draft or mark for review. Scope control (one user, drafts not sends, rules before heavy LLM) is what makes a strong bootcamp delivery on time possible. You can paste this into Notion, Google Doc, or your capstone report as-is. If you want, next turn can be only a 1-page HLD diagram in Mermaid (still no code) for slides. (No project repo was analyzed for this answer.)